      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at this contract for a freelance gig and i don't really get what \"indemnification\" means. can u explain it in plain english?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification, in plain English, is basically a promise where one party agrees to cover the costs and losses of another party if something goes wrong. Think of it like this: if a problem arises, the indemnifying party steps in and pays the bill, instead of the other party having to foot the whole bill themselves. It's a way to shift the risk around, making sure someone else takes the financial hit if a specific bad thing happens.",
